Process Guide

 
💡
This section has been created to give you an overview of how we expect you to manage and organise yourself to ensure the smooth operations of your day to day activities and to ensure continuity in working style and output.
 

Chatter Dashboard

Each chatter has their own dashboard which has a link to their sales form, the creators they are covering, their schedule and any other relevant information. This is your go to location when starting your shift. Example chatter dashboard:
 
 

Hours and shifts

To know what hours, shifts and accounts you are working on, go to your chatter dashboard and scroll down to schedule, as per the image above. All team members work on either 8, 9 or 10 hour shifts with 30 minutes on each side of the shift for admin time. Admin time is an opportunity to take your time and get comfortable with your work, it is a time to:
•
Check your creators social accounts
•
Check notes from handover of the previous chatter
•
Check if your creator(s) has dropped any new content on their OnlyFans page or vault
•
Check to see the newsfeed of any of your creators for latest updates (see the creator dashboard)
 

Shift Handover

When you have finished your shift and are completing your admin time, make sure to add any relevant notes and updates to your Slack/Telegram groups. This is where other chatters can come to read the latest ongoings of subs, content and news related to that creator.
 

Creator Calendar

Each creator has a calendar where chatters can add information with timestamps that are relevant for the creator. For example, if a particular sub has scheduled a sexting session, or if a particular sub has a payday and will be online, etc. These are critical pieces of information which can be used to ensure the team are on top of each opportunity that is presented. See below example, which can be found in the creator dashboard:
 
 

Custom Content

Once a sub has tipped and confirmed the details of the custom content request, complete the Custom Content Form on the creator dashboard. The request will go directly to the account manager and or creator so make sure the information is as accurate and clear as possible. Not all creators do both video calls AND custom videos, so be aware not to agree something with a sub which is not possible.
 
 

Chatting Guidelines

•
If another creator messages you, do not message back, delete the chat - this is not relevant for your shift
•
When you sell or share content where there is a second person in the video on OnlyFans, you must tag the second person in the video on the message chat. This is because every person in a video must be verified by OnlyFans.
•
If an Account Manager messages the chat, they are either uploading content or speaking to the Team Leader, do not message back, just ignore it
•
The word “meet” is banned on OF, do not talk about meeting off-platform, turn the conversation around
•
Try not ask more than one question in a message, keep it simple, like a WhatsApp conversation
•
Whenever you are going to sell content that is in a script or pre-recorded, say to the sub “1 sec” or “let me record this for you”
•
If a sub has finished a script, add that sub to the list for the script, for example list “Script 6”. This is so that we know how many times a script has been used
•
If a conversation was had with a sub and for your new shift you see this chat, do not start with “hey, wyd”, bring something up from the earlier conversation
•
Chatters NEED to watch the lives so they know whats going on for the chats thereafter (either OnlyFans, TikTok, or IG lives)
